one for a specific candidate surface.

\paragraph{C.76: surviving and aggregate bank net worth.}
The source level row for surviving bankers is
\begin{equation}
N_{e,t}
=\theta\left[
R^k_tQ_{t-1}K_{b,t-1}
+R^b_tQ^b_{t-1}B_{b,t-1}
-R^d_{t-1}D_{t-1}
-R^L_{t-1}L^q_{t-1}
\right].
\label{eq:bgs-c76-level-repeat}
\end{equation}
Use the lagged balance sheet to replace deposits:
\begin{equation}
D_{t-1}
=Q_{t-1}K_{b,t-1}
+Q^b_{t-1}B_{b,t-1}
-N_{t-1}-L^q_{t-1}.
\label{eq:bgs-c76-lagged-balance-expanded}
\end{equation}
Substituting \eqref{eq:bgs-c76-lagged-balance-expanded} into
\eqref{eq:bgs-c76-level-repeat} gives
\begin{align}
