economic role. The capital and bond terms are excess-return payoffs on
lagged bank-held assets. The liquidity term is a funding-spread saving from
borrowing from the central bank rather than deposits. The final term is the
safe return on inherited net worth. After balanced-growth scaling, C.76 is
