The last $N_n n_{n,t}$ term means the displayed row is aggregate bank net
worth after entry. If one wants the surviving-bank law alone, that entrant
term must be omitted. This distinction matters because the new-bank asset-base
interpretation changes aggregate net worth through exactly that entrant term.

