\paragraph{C.82--C.83: purchase residuals from asset clearing.}
Asset-market clearing gives
\[
K_t=K_{b,t}+K_{h,t}+K_{cb,t},
\qquad
B_t=B_{b,t}+B_{h,t}+B_{cb,t}.
\]
After dividing by aggregate steady-state stocks, the capital-purchase residual
is
\begin{equation}
x_{k,t}
=k_t-\frac{K_b}{K}k_{b,t}-\frac{K_h}{K}k_{h,t},
\label{eq:bgs-c82-derived-ladder}
\end{equation}
and the bond-purchase residual is
\begin{equation}
x_{b,t}
=b_t-\frac{B_b}{B}b_{b,t}-\frac{B_h}{B}b_{h,t}.
\label{eq:bgs-c83-derived-ladder}
\end{equation}
The residual interpretation is essential. These rows do not say that the
central bank optimizes over \(x_{k,t}\) or \(x_{b,t}\) inside the bank problem.
They say that after total supply, bank holdings, and household holdings are
known, the remaining stock is the central-bank purchase quantity.

\paragraph{C.84--C.85: conversion to GDP-scaled observables.}
The purchase residuals are converted to observable units by
\begin{equation}
\widetilde K_{cb,t}=x_{k,t}\frac{QK}{4Y},
\qquad
\widetilde B_{cb,t}=x_{b,t}\frac{Q^bB}{4Y}.
\label{eq:bgs-c84-c85-derived-ladder}
\end{equation}
The denominator \(4Y\) is a quarterly-to-annual GDP scaling convention. It is
not part of the bank incentive constraint and not part of the household
direct-holding FOC. Thus QE measurement has to be attached at the observation
boundary, not pushed backward into asset pricing.

paragraphs.text:
\paragraph{C.82--C.83: purchase residuals from asset clearing.}
Asset-market clearing gives
\[
K_t=K_{b,t}+K_{h,t}+K_{cb,t},
\qquad
B_t=B_{b,t}+B_{h,t}+B_{cb,t}.
\]
After dividing by aggregate steady-state stocks, the capital-purchase residual
is
\begin{equation}
x_{k,t}
=k_t-\frac{K_b}{K}k_{b,t}-\frac{K_h}{K}k_{h,t},
\label{eq:bgs-c82-derived-ladder}
\end{equation}
and the bond-purchase residual is
\begin{equation}
x_{b,t}
=b_t-\frac{B_b}{B}b_{b,t}-\frac{B_h}{B}b_{h,t}.
\label{eq:bgs-c83-derived-ladder}
\end{equation}
The residual interpretation is essential. These rows do not say that the
central bank optimizes over \(x_{k,t}\) or \(x_{b,t}\) inside the bank problem.
They say that after total supply, bank holdings, and household holdings are
known, the remaining stock is the central-bank purchase quantity.

